{"title_page": "Chamara Janaraj Peiris", "text_new": "{{short description|Sri Lankan director}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Chamara Janaraj Peiris <br> \u0da0\u0dcf\u0db8\u0dbb \u0da2\u0db1\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\n| other_names   =\n| image         = \n| background    = \n| image_size    = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1970|01|14}}\n| birth_name    = Chamara Janaraj Peiris \n| birth_place   = [[Colombo]], Sri Lanka\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   = \n| resting_place = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|display=inline,title}} -->\n| nationality   = [[Sri Lanka]]n\n| education     = [[Royal College, Colombo]]\n| residence     = \n| years_active  = 1991\u2013present\n| party         = \n| spouse        = \n| children      = \n| awards        = \n| signature     = \n| website       = \n| footnotes     = \n| occupation    = Director, screen writer\n}}\n\n'''Chamara Janaraj Peiris''' ([[:si:\u0da0\u0dcf\u0db8\u0dbb \u0da2\u0db1\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca|\u0da0\u0dcf\u0db8\u0dbb \u0da2\u0db1\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca]]; born 14 January 1970), is a Sri Lankan journalist, screenplay writer, television director and [[filmmaker]]. He has produced several critically acclaimed television serials such as ''Piyavi'', ''Ayal'', ''Batahira Ahasa'' and ''Raahu''.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://mirrorarts.lk/news/4848-chamara-janaraj-190224 | title=Chamara Janaraj coming silver screen | publisher=Mirror Arts | accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm8898868/ | title=Chamara Janaraj Peiris | publisher=IMDb | accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref> Currently he is the Creative Director of Pix and Words (Pvt) Ltd.<ref name= chamara>{{cite web | url=http://www.chamarajanaraj.com/ | title=I am Chamara Peiris | publisher=Chamara Peiris official website | accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nPeiris was born on 14 January 1970 in Colombo as the only child of the family. He completed education from [[Royal College, Colombo]]. In his last year at the school, he was awarded the best student by the President. His father died on 17 March 2011.<ref name= janaraj>{{cite web | url=https://www.dinamina.lk/2018/09/20/\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc1\u0dda\u0dc2\u0dcf\u0d82\u0d9c/60649/\u0dad\u0db8\u0dcf-\u0dad\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dc0-\u0db4\u0ddd\u0dc2\u0dab\u0dba-\u0d9a\u0dbb-\u0d9c\u0dad-\u0dba\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dba\u0dd2 | title=He must feed himself | publisher=Dinamina | accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter completing education, he went Russia with a scholarship to obtain Bachelor of Science in Architecture from Moscow Architecture Academy in 1997. Then he completed MSc in Landscape Design from [[University of Moratuwa]] in 2003. He worked as [[SLBC]] correspondent in Moscow for six years from 1991 to 1997.<ref name= chamara /><ref name= janaraj />\n\nIn 2009, Peries directed his maiden television serial ''Ayal''. Then he directed his next serial ''Piyavi'' in 2011 and ''Yaya 4'' in 2012. All three serials were critically acclaimed and had 30 nominations in many local festivals. Since then, Peiris has contributed with many popular serials including ''Acid'', ''VVIP'', ''Batahira Ahasa'' and ''Raahu''.<ref name= chamara /><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.aniwa.lk/2016/04/30/7-banned-books-films-teledramas-in-sri-lanka/ | title=Banned films, serials and novels | publisher=Aniwa | accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref><ref name= janaraj />\n\nApart from television serials, Peiris involved in many advertisements, documentary programs as well as a journalist in Associate Newspapers Ceylon Ltd. (ANCL) since 1997 to 2010. He wrote series of articles called ''13th Page'' and articles on Extraterrestrial beings and the Theory of Universe published in Dinamina Newspaper. Then he worked as Director Programming for Stein Studios from 2016 to 2017. While working in ANCL, Peiris contributed in many positions such as administrative officer, managing editor, layout editor and graphic designer.<ref name= chamara /><ref name= janaraj />\n\nIn 2019, he made debut cinema direction with the film ''Uthuru Sulanga''.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/features-teledramas/2020/01/09/14226/\u0dbd\u0dda\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca-\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dc0-\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0da7\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1-\u0db6\u0dd1 | title=\u0dbd\u0dda\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0dbb\u0dc0\u0da7\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd1 | publisher=Sarasaviya| accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref> The film is yet to release.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://ceylontoday.lk/features-more/4797?fbclid=IwAR3AEouPupq8C0-h3H_Y9L2_ydMFKgN0svuT-lplbFx4d2VlJ7SpDJhBWak | title=Winds of Change | publisher=Ceylon Today | accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\nPeiris has won and nominated for several awards at teledrama festivals for Best director and best script.<ref name= chamara /><ref name= janaraj />\n\n===State Film Awards===\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n|| 2011 ||| ''Ayal'' || Best Teledrama Director || {{won}} \n|-\n|| 2011 ||| ''Ayal'' || Best Teledrama Scriptwriter || {{won}} \n|-\n|| 2012 ||| ''Piyavi'' || Best Teledrama Director || {{nominated}} \n|-\n|| 2012 ||| ''Piyavi'' || Best Teledrama Scriptwriter || {{nominated}} \n|-\n|| 2013 ||| ''Yaya 4'' || Best Teledrama Scriptwriter || {{nominated}} \n{{End}}\n\n===[[Raigam Tele'es]]===\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n|| 2010 ||| ''Ayal'' || Jury Special Award || {{won}} \n|-\n|| 2010 ||| ''Ayal'' || Best Teledrama Scriptwriter || {{nominated}} \n|-\n|| 2011 ||| ''Piyavi'' || Best Teledrama Scriptwriter || {{nominated}} \n|-\n|| 2012 ||| ''Piyavi'' || Best Teledrama Director || {{nominated}} \n{{End}}\n\n===[[Sumathi Awards]]===\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n|| 2010 ||| ''Piyavi'' || Jury Special Award || {{won}} \n{{End}}\n\n==Directed serials==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Tele serial !! Ref. \n|-\n| 2009 || ''Ayal'' || \n|-\n| 2011 || ''Piyavi'' || <ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.pressreader.com/sri-lanka/sunday-times-sri-lanka/20120916/284021894250259 | title=\u2018Piyavi\u2019 rate popular chart | publisher=Sunday Times | accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2012 || ''Yaya 4'' || \n|-\n| 2014 || ''Acid'' || \n|-\n| 2014 || ''Red Rain'' || \n|-\n| 2015 || ''VVIP'' || \n|-\n| 2015 || ''Pulse'' || \n|-\n| 2015 || ''A330'' || \n|-\n| 2016 || ''Andromeda'' || \n|-\n| 2016 || ''Batahira Ahasa'' || <ref>{{cite web | url=http://archives.sarasaviya.lk/2017/11/16/?fn=sa1711161 | title=Another teledrama from Chamara Janaraj | publisher=Sarasaviya | accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017 || ''Thrimana'' || <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dailynews.lk/2017/11/07/entertainment/133566/\u2018smart\u2019-choices | title=\u2018Smart\u2019 choices | publisher=Daily News | accessdate=8 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019 || ''Raahu'' || \n|}\n\n==Directed films==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Ref. \n|-\n| TBD || ''Uthuru Sulanga'' || \n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Peiris, Chamara Janaraj}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan film directors]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan directors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Sri Lankan director}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Chamara Janaraj Peiris <br> \u0da0\u0dcf\u0db8\u0dbb \u0da2\u0db1\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\n| other_names   =\n| image         = \n| background    = \n| image_size    = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1970|01|14}}\n| birth_name    = Chamara Janaraj Peiris \n| birth_place   = [[Colombo]], Sri Lanka\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   = \n| resting_place = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|display=inline,title}} -->\n| nationality   = [[Sri L